00:15:29.340 --> 00:15:32.340
Essentially, there's going to be new data when that report reruns.

00:15:32.340 --> 00:15:37.380
It's going to be a new HTML output and that will basically publish on top of the previous

00:15:37.380 --> 00:15:41.820
version. But what's really nice about Connect is it actually keeps track of historical

00:15:41.820 --> 00:15:45.739
versions that you published and you can always revert back to a previous version or

00:15:45.739 --> 00:15:51.020
download that previous version's bundle so you can reproduce a previous version of that

00:15:51.020 --> 00:15:57.380
report. So by default, yes, it will kind of build on top every single time you publish

00:15:57.419 --> 00:15:57.940
a new report.

